<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172064>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 6. 1 – 2. Isoneuromyia heads, lateral view, showing general shapes, antennal flagellomeres and vestiture removed. 1. I. splendida, n. sp. 2. I. yorki, n. sp. 3 – 6. Isoneuromyia antennae, lateral view. 3. I. nigerrima, n. sp. 4. I. splendida, n. sp. 5. I. polybioides (Edwards). 6. I. glabra, n. sp." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/172064/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172066>
    dc:description "FIGURES 11 – 19. Isoneuromyia thoraces, dorsal view. 11. I. brunettii, n. sp. 12. I. flava, n. sp. 13. I. glabra, n. sp. 14. I. matilei, n. sp. 15. I. nigribasis, n. sp. 16. I. pallidopsis, n. sp. 17. I. splendida, n. sp. 18. I. xanthina (Edwards). 19. I. yorki, n. sp." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/172066/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.172069>
    dc:description "FIGURE 34. Isoneuromyia splendida, n. sp. A. Male genitalia, dorsal view. B. Detail of apex of gonostylus, showing minute teeth in between larger teeth." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/172069/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

